    "description": {
      "value": "<p>At 20th level, whenever the cavalier makes a&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/combat#TOC-Charge\">charge</a>&nbsp;attack while mounted, he deals double the normal amount of&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/combat#TOC-Damage\">damage</a>&nbsp;(or triple if using a lance). In addition, if the cavalier confirms a critical hit on a&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/combat#TOC-Charge\">charge</a>&nbsp;attack while mounted, the target is&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/conditions#TOC-Stunned\">stunned</a>&nbsp;for 1d4 rounds. A&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/combat#TOC-Will\">Will</a>&nbsp;save reduces this to&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/conditions#TOC-Staggered\">staggered</a>&nbsp;for 1d4 rounds. The DC is equal to 10 + the cavalierâ€™s base&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/combat#TOC-Attack-Bonus\">attack bonus</a>.</p>",
